cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the problem of preserving privacy in a multivariate source coding scenario, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a common link and private links suggests a potential application in multimedia communication (cs.MM) or social networks (cs.SI). The paper also presents a characterization of achievable rates-equivocation tuples, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization (cs.DS).
